text: Bisham (said "Bissam") is a village in Windsor and Maidenhead, Berkshire, England, UK. It is on River Thames. Across the river is Marlow in Buckinghamshire. In 2001 there were 1,149 people living in Bisham. == References == Category:Towns in Berkshire Category:Civil parishes in Berkshire Category:Royal Borough of Windsor and Maidenhead
